Constructor Detail

V3DBundle

public V3DBundle(String front,
                 String right,
                 String back,
                 String left)
Creates a V3DBundle with front, back, left and right view points. The type is BUNDLE_TYPE_LEVEL by default. Top and bottom view points can be added via the setTopBottom(..), setTopOnly and setBottomOnly methods.

Parameters:
front - location of the front view image relative to whatever file system is being used.
right - location of the right view image relative to whatever file system is being used.
back - location of the back view image relative to whatever file system is being used.
left - location of the left view image relative to whatever file system is being used.
Method Detail

setTopBottom

public void setTopBottom(String top,
                         String bottom)
                  throws IllegalStateException
Sets the location of both the top and bottom view points in this V3DBundle. This method corresponds to BUNDLE_TYPE_360.

Parameters:
top - the location of the top image relative to whatever file system is being used.
bottom - the location of the bottom image relative to whatever file system is being used.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if this V3DBundle has been locked in a final state and can no longer be modified.
IllegalStateException

setTopOnly

public void setTopOnly(String top)
                throws IllegalStateException
Sets the location of the top view point in this V3DBundle. This method corresponds to BUNDLE_TYPE_TOP. This method will ensure that the bottom image value is reset to null.

Parameters:
top - the location of the image relative to whatever file system is being used.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if this V3DBundle has been locked in a final state and can no longer be modified.
IllegalStateException

setBottomOnly

public void setBottomOnly(String bottom)
                   throws IllegalStateException
Sets the location of the bottom view point in this V3DBundle. This method corresponds to BUNDLE_TYPE_BOTTOM. This method will ensure that the top image value is reset to null.

Parameters:
bottom - the location of the image relative to whatever file system is being used.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if this V3DBundle has been locked in a final state and can no longer be modified.
IllegalStateException

resetToLevel

public void resetToLevel()
                  throws IllegalStateException
Discards any values set for the bottom and top image locations and resets the type to BUNDLE_TYPE_LEVEL.

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if this V3DBundle has been locked in a final state and can no longer be modified.
IllegalStateException

getFinalImageArray

public String[] getFinalImageArray()
Returns the image-name data of this V3DBundle in a String[]. This method calls lock() if this V3DBundle has not yet been locked. The returned array is sorted in correspondence to the TOP, BOTTOM, RIGHT, LEFT, BACK, FRONT fields.

Returns:
an ordered array of String image locations sorted by 3D view position.
See Also:
lock()

getBundleType

public int getBundleType()
Returns this V3DBundle's type (as specified in class). This method calls lock() if this V3DBundle has not yet been locked.

Returns:
the type specification of this V3DBundle.
See Also:
lock()

lock

public void lock()
Manually lock this V3DBundle so it will no longer be modifiable and can forever hold its state.

isLocked

public boolean isLocked()
Returns the current modification state of the V3DBundle.

Returns:
true if this V3DBundle has been locked in a final state, false otherwise.

copy

public V3DBundle copy()
Returns a direct, unlocked copy of this V3DBundle. This method ignores modification state, so this bundle will be copied regardless of whether or not lock() has been called and will not affect the current state of this V3DBundle.
